It seems certain that about this time a stage was erected in the Circus at the redimamur, and the first three days of the festival were henceTorth occupied ,with recitations, music, and dancing. Pertormers from Etruria, called ludeones, danced to the music of the flute without words or descriptiva action ; hut the strolling minstrels os Latium (grassatores, spoliatores) soon took advantage of the stage to recito their chants with appropriate music and gesture. These performances were named from their miscellaneous character Santrae ¹. They were composed in the rugged Saturnian metra, with no connected plot, and did not admit os dialogue.

Fabulae Atellanae. A nearer approach to dramatic form was made in the Fabulae Atellanae, broad tarces with stock characters, e. g. Maccus, Pappus, Bucco, and Dossenus, analogous to the clown, pantaloon, and harlequin of an English pantomimo. Each character had its traditional mask, and the pieces were originally played only by amateurs at private theatricals; hut when translations from Greek dramas had monopolised the Roman stage, the Atellan sarce was adopted
